<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p>The 'go to' short break destination for UK skiers and Boarders, France has it all, large ski areas, short transfers and plenty of accommodation choices.</p>
<h2><span style="color: #002f5a;">Chamonix</span></h2>
<p>One of the original short duration resorts due to its close proximity and quick motorway links to Geneva. A favourite destination due to its extensive skiing across 4 areas of Brevent which is accessed by cable car from the town, La Tour, Argentiere and Les Houche are all easily accessed by a regular free ski bus service.</p>
<p>Chamonix does have a reputation for extreme but the ski areas have something for all and are ideal for a group wanting to hit the slopes hard and enjoy the Apres ski that can be found in town. Many people also opt to ski or board the Valley Blanche which is a famous off piste run from the top of the Aiguille du Midi, Les Houche is one of the satellite villages of Chamonix and has easy links into the town and to all of the ski areas of the Valley De Chamonix Mont Blanc Mont Blanc area</p>
